Reasoning: The paper deals with resource allocation and information exchange between competing users and a resource controller. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses achievable schemes and rate distortion functions, which are common topics in the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions potential applications in multimedia (cs.MM), which further supports the inclusion of this sub-category.
